n be difficult and takes a lot of time. I recommend reading through successful teams code from this year or past to get a better scope, but this seems like it would get the job done. If anyone else sees something I missed definitely point it out.</p>
<p>I would like to say that yagsl probably doesn’t need an inverter, but our team uses the AdvantageKit template so its possible I misunderstand something in the docs.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-07-25T07:03:40.036Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":116,"readers_count":115,"score":33.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":504578,"topic_slug":"intake-programming","display_username":"Owen Tharp","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":68308,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/intake-programming/504578/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3689800,"name":"Tim Winters","username":"ArchdukeTim","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/archduketim/{size}/256125_2.png","created_at":"2025-07-25T14:36:42.694Z","cooked":"<p>Firstly, I would avoid subclassing <code>Command</code>, and instead use the <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/commands.html#included-command-types" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">factory methods</a>. It lets you keep commands within the subsystem that they’re used in, and results in simpler robot code overall.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">// IntakePosition.java
angulo = subsystem.getDistance();
output = subsystem.calculateOutput(angulo, setpoint);

if(angulo &lt; 55){
  if(output &gt; 0) output = 0.0;

  if(setpoint &gt; 55.0) setpoint = 55.0;
}

if(angulo &gt; 230.0){
  if(output &gt; 0.0) output = 0.0;

  if(setpoint &gt; 230.0) setpoint = 230.0;
}

subsystem.setPosition(output);
</code></pre>
<p>This seems like you’re trying to set soft-limits on your intake subsystem to avoid it from goin too far in one direction or the other? Though some of the equalities don’t fully align with that (such as if the angle was &lt; 55, but output was also &lt; 0), but I could be misunderstanding the purpose.</p>
<p>Consider what would happen if you wanted a different command that also moved the intake. You’d have to repeat this limit logic in that command too. It would be better if you included this logic in the <code>setPosition</code> method of the intake subsystem so that any time you try and set the position, it checked for the limits.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">// IntakePosition.java
private IntakeSubsystem subsystem;
private double setpoint;
private DutyCycleEncoder encoder = subsystem.getEncoder();
</code></pre>
<p>the third line will throw a NullPointerException since <code>subsystem</code> doesn’t exist until the constructor is called. You need to move the assignment of encoder to the constructor.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">// Intake.java
public void setPosition(double saida){
    intake.set(saida);
}
</code></pre>
<p>The name of this function is <code>setPosition</code>, but the <code>set</code> method of spark max controls its duty-cycle, or percentage output.</p>
<p>I would generally recommend adjusting the structure of your subsystem and command to have a method that takes in a position, calculates the output for the motor, and then applies that output to the motor. Rather than having 3 different methods and requiring you to coordinate between them.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">//RobotContainer.java
public final XboxController DriveController = new XboxController(Controllers.DRIVER_CONTROLLER);
public final XboxController intakeController = new XboxController(Controllers.INTAKE_CONTROLLER);

private void configureBindings() {

    new JoystickButton(intakeController, 10).whileTrue(new IntakeSpeed(intake, 0.7));
    new JoystickButton(intakeController, 9).whileTrue(new IntakeSpeed(intake, -0.7));

    new JoystickButton(intakeController, 1).onTrue(new IntakePosition(intake, 120));
  }
</code></pre>
<p>Instead of <code>XboxController</code>, use <code>CommandXboxController</code> which exposes the buttons as triggers for use with command based bindings.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":4,"updated_at":"2025-07-25T14:36:42.694Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":88,"readers_count":87,"score":67.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":504578,"topic_slug":"intake-programming","display_username":"Tim Winters","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/commandbased/commands.html#included-command-types","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Commands — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":7}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":19820,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"78 AIR Strike Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/intake-programming/504578/3","custom_user_title":"78 AIR Strike Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3690096,"name":"Murilo Miranda Santos","username":"murilo404","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/49beb7/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-07-25T21:25:45.663Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for helping me! But I need to configure the encoder and <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Deriva